be-construction: There is no uninflected finite 'be'; the only finite verb is 'saw'.
resultant-done: No preverbal 'done' marking completive aspect appears.
finna: No 'finna' or equivalent imminent future marker is present.
come: No stance/evaluative 'come' preceding a VP; 'come' does not appear.
double-modal: No sequence of two modals (e.g., 'might could') occurs.
multiple-neg: There are no negative elements in the clause.
neg-inversion: No clause-initial negative auxiliary preceding the subject.
n-inv-neg-concord: No negative subject and negative auxiliary combination is present.
aint: The form 'ain’t' is not used as a negator.
zero-3sg-pres-s: No 3sg present-tense verb; the finite verb 'saw' is past with a plural subject 'we'.
is-was-gen: No nonstandard use of 'is/was'; the clause uses 'saw' as the finite verb.
zero-pl-s: The plural noun 'helicopters' carries plural -s; no clear plural NP lacks -s.
double-object: No personal dative pattern (subject + coreferential object pronoun + NP) occurs.
wh-qu1: There is no WH-question; the sentence is declarative.
wh-qu2: No WH-clause with nonstandard inversion appears.
existential-it: There is no existential 'it'; 'it' does not appear.
demonstrative-them: No 'them' used as a demonstrative determiner occurs.
appositive-pleonastic-pronoun: No NP is followed by a co-referential pronoun in the same clause.

sentence: We was trying to wave thems down, seem like they was getting the ones over on the rooftop, cause I did saw a few-  I could look down the street and see a few on- on- on the rooftop.

be-construction: No uninflected habitual 'be' occurs (e.g., 'be V-ing'); all instances are 'was' forms.
resultant-done: There is no preverbal 'done' marking completive aspect.
come: No preverbal stance 'come' construction appears; 'come' is absent.

multiple-neg: No clause contains more than one negative element; there is no negative concord.
